  "title": "Class 4 Driver (5.5 Days)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Drive and operate company vehicles, including 24-footer (10-ton truck with tailgate) and 14-footer (3.5-ton truck)</li>\n  <li>Carry out daily deliveries and collections efficiently and safely, ensuring goods are handled with care</li>\n  <li>Perform basic vehicle checks and maintenance to ensure the truck is in good working condition</li>\n  <li>Assist with loading and unloading of goods when required</li>\n  <li>Ensure all delivery documents are completed and submitted accurately</li>\n  <li>Follow assigned delivery schedules and instructions from the logistics team</li>\n  <li>Comply with all traffic regulations, safety procedures, and company policies</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Additional Notes:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>May occasionally be required to work beyond standard hours or during off-peak hours; advance notice will be provided</li>\n  <li>Overtime allowances will be given for work done during late hours or on irregular schedules</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess a valid Singapore Class 3 or Class 4 driving license</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of local roads and traffic regulations</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
